        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Livelihood Opportunity Promotion Scheme (Scheduled Tribe)&quot; scheme was launched by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Uttarakhand. It aims to promote sustainable self-employment and income generation among Scheduled Tribe individuals by supporting viable livelihood projects. Under this scheme, financial assistance, including a bank loan is provided to the beneficiaries for setting up income-generating units with a total project cost between ₹50,000 and ₹2,00,000. \n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Financial Assistance:**\n\n\n\n  - Project Cost: Between ₹50,000/- and ₹2,00,000/-.\n  - Bank Loan: 60% of the project cost\n  - Margin Money: 30% of the project cost, repayable at 7% annual interest in 60 monthly installments\n  - Grant: Up to ₹50,000/-.\n\n\n> **Beneficiary Contribution:**\n\n\n\n  - No contribution for project cost up to ₹1,00,000/-\n  - 10% contribution for project cost between ₹1,01,000/- and ₹2,00,000/-\n\n\n<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to promote self-employment among Scheduled Tribe individuals through financial support, including loans, margin money, and grants.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
