            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The \"Livelihood Opportunity Promotion Scheme (Scheduled Tribe)\" scheme was launched by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Uttarakhand. It aims to promote sustainable self-employment and income generation among Scheduled Tribe individuals by supporting viable livelihood projects. Under this scheme, financial assistance, including a bank loan is provided to the beneficiaries for setting up income-generating units with a total project cost between ₹50,000 and ₹2,00,000. "
